27 ARTICLE 16. SOCIAL MEDIA PROVIDERS
28 Chapter 1. Definitions
29 Sec. 1. The definitions in this chapter apply throughout this
30 article.
31 Sec. 2. "Account", with respect to a social media platform,
32 means a unique identifier that:
33 (1) is provided to a person by the owner or operator of the
34 social media platform; and
35 (2) enables the person to:
36 (A) access the social media platform; or
37 (B) access functionality of the social media platform that is
38 not available without use of the unique identifier.
39 Sec. 3. (a) "Covered social media provider", or "provider",
40 means a person that:
41 (1) owns or operates a social media platform; and
42 (2) collectively with any parent, subsidiary, or affiliate of the
2026 IN 1178—LS 6789/DI 119

7
1 person, generated at least one billion dollars ($1,000,000,000)
2 in gross revenues, worldwide, in one (1) or more of the
3 immediately preceding three (3) years.
4 (b) The term does not include a communications service
5 provider (as defined in IC 8-1-2.6-13).
6 Sec. 4. "Indiana account holder", with respect to a social media
7 platform, means an individual:
8 (1) to whom the owner or operator of the social media
9 platform has provided an account with the social media
10 platform;
11 (2) who is:
12 (A) a resident of Indiana; or
13 (B) located in Indiana at the time the individual accesses
14 the social media platform; and
15 (3) who the owner or operator of the social media platform
16 knows, or reasonably should know, to be:
17 (A) a resident of Indiana; or
18 (B) located in Indiana at the time the individual accesses
19 the social media platform.
20 Sec. 5. "Linked account", with respect to an individual's
21 account with a social media platform, means another account with
22 the social media platform that the individual has designated,
23 through a means provided by the social media platform, as an
24 account:
25 (1) from which the individual wishes to receive content;
26 (2) content from which the individual wishes the social media
27 platform to include in recommendations for content provided
28 to the user by the social media platform; or
29 (3) with which the individual wishes to associate the
30 individual's account.
31 Sec. 6. "Minor" means an individual who:
32 (1) is less than fourteen (14) years of age; and
33 (2) is not legally emancipated.
34 Sec. 7. "Parent", with regard to a minor, includes any legal
35 guardian of the minor.
36 Sec. 8. (a) "Personal information", with regard to an individual,
37 means any of the following:
38 (1) Information regarding the individual that is described in
39 15 U.S.C. 6501(8).
40 (2) A record of, or derived from, the individual's:
41 (A) online activity;
42 (B) online search history; or
2026 IN 1178—LS 6789/DI 119

