1 technology and data available to the covered social media
2 provider;
3 to determine the age of the Indiana account holder.
4 (b) Subject to subsection (d):
5 (1) if a covered social media provider is able to determine
6 under subsection (a) with eighty percent (80%) confidence
7 that an Indiana account holder is fourteen (14) years of age or
8 older, the covered social media provider may consider the
9 Indiana account holder to not be a minor for purposes of this
10 article; and
11 (2) if the covered social media provider is not able to
